text: Jacob Parsons (27 February 1903 – 1953) was an English professional footballer who played in the Football League for Accrington Stanley, Barrow, Exeter City, Mansfield Town, Southport and Thames. ==References== Category:1903 births Category:1953 deaths Category:English footballers Category:Association football forwards Category:English Football League players Category:Southport F.C. players Category:Barrow A.F.C. players Category:Exeter City F.C. players Category:Thames A.F.C. players Category:Mansfield Town F.C. players Category:Rotherham United F.C. players Category:Accrington Stanley F.C.
